-- AngioDynamics agrees to buy Rita Medical for $220 mln
-- 
-- Tue Nov 28, 2006 6:50am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2006/11/28/us-ritamedical-takeover-angiodynamics-idUSWNAS429120061128

 

 (Reuters) - Medical device maker AngioDynamics Inc. ( ANGO.O ) on Tuesday said it agreed to buy Rita Medical Systems Inc. RITA.O for $220 million in cash and stock. 

 Excluding transaction and one-time integration costs, AngioDynamics expects the deal to be neutral to fiscal 2007 earnings and to add about 5 cents a share to fiscal 2008 earnings, AngioDynamics said in a statement. The acquisition is expected to close in the first calendar quarter of 2007, the company added. Thetransaction includes the assumption of about $3.3 million in net debt. (Reporting by Kuncheria Cholemkeril in Bangalore)